## Second-Year Monitoring Enhancements

The first authorization year's monitoring program was designed before operations began. The second year's monitoring program should incorporate the lessons that eight months of actual operation produced:

**Enhancement 1 — Semi-annual audit log completeness test (added):** The AU-12 finding was not detected by any automated monitoring mechanism. It required a human-initiated test procedure. The semi-annual completeness test institutionalizes this type of proactive assurance check.

**Enhancement 2 — CM-3 compliance rate metric (formalized):** The M-002 and A-7 findings revealed that CM-3 compliance was a behavioral gap, not a technical gap. Formalizing the CM-3 compliance rate metric — number of security-relevant changes preceded by ISSO notification versus discovered post-hoc — creates the measurement that makes the gap visible in the metrics dashboard.

**Enhancement 3 — Phishing simulation effectiveness metrics (new):** KRI-AT-1 (click rate) and the reporting rate are new metrics that did not exist in year one. Adding them to the quarterly monitoring cycle closes the AT-2 effectiveness measurement gap.

**Enhancement 4 — CP-3 retention check (semi-annual):** Informal but documented. Adds behavioral assurance for the contingency plan training that completion records alone cannot provide.

**Enhancement 5 — RPO improvement (proposed):** Daily S3 export (reducing maximum RPO from 7 days to 1 day for full environment reconstruction). Under development; pending Health IT Manager and AO approval. If approved, the quarterly backup restoration test procedure will be updated to test the daily export restoration path.

